    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-02-04T08:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-02-03T04:07:00-05:00" n="498"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d498">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/3800: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1919-02-04T08:35:00-05:00"
                            notBefore="1919-02-03T14:00:00+04:53">
                            <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received February 4, 1919, 8:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following from [<persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName> at] Omsk.</p>
                <p>“83, February 3, 2 p.m. Government has asked that an American officer be attached
                    to commission which is proceeding Chita to inquire into
                        <persName>Semenoff</persName> conduct. French and English representatives
                    here will comply providing other interested powers do so. I have referred
                    request to <persName corresp="#p_GMGWS1">General Graves</persName> through
                    Captain Schuyler.<note n="21" xml:id="d498fn21">Capt. Montgomery Schuyler,
                        U.S.A., on duty at Omsk.</note> I understand this whole commission is to sit
                    [under?] Japanese protection. <persName corresp="#p_HEL1"
                    >Harris</persName>.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RPS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
